Deputy Chief Justice Raymond Zondo made a statement about the events that took place during Tuesday's evening session when the cross-examination of Minister Pravin Gordhan by Advocate Dali Mpofu got a little heated. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Deputy Chief Justice Raymond Zondo says he has never heard a lawyer tell someone to "shut up"  during a proceeding or hearing. Zondo has expressed his disappointment at the exchange on Tuesday evening. WATCH: State capture inquiry gets heated The deputy chief justice said he views the statements Mpofu made -- telling Public Enterprises Minister Pravin Gordhan and his legal representative, Advocate Michelle le Roux to "shut up" -- in a very serious light, adding that what happened was unacceptable. "The right to cross-examine and the right to re-examine are all part of the right to be heard, the right to be heard is not absolute," he said.